name: Punjabi kitchen Bar & Restaurant

reviews.review_text:
Nice place for North Indian and Goan cuisine. We got the Fish Curry and the Fish Thali - both pretty tasty. Wasn’t too busy when we arrived so food came pretty quick.  Friendly and attentive staff. Total bill came to 734 ( including a bottle of water).

Able to sit in a closed AC room or open sitting near to the road where you get a nice breeze.

Would recommend.

Fantastic food! We ordered the dal makhani, the chicken kadai, and the chili paneer. Everything was so bledy good. But once again, we fooled ourselves into thinking we could easily take down all of this food. Alas, we were not even bledy close. We left here so stuffed, that my friend literally had to roll me out of there like a giant exercise ball.

A decent option near Calangute beach which serves north indian food late at night. Food was decent as was the service.
Overall, a decent option.

description:
### Punjabi Kitchen Bar & Restaurant: A Culinary Gem in Calangute

Nestled in the lively atmosphere of Calangute, Goa, Punjabi Kitchen Bar & Restaurant has garnered an impressive rating of 4.8 from over 7,000 reviewers, making it a favored spot for both locals and tourists alike. Specializing in North Indian and Goan cuisine, this restaurant is frequently highlighted for its scrumptious **fish curry**, **fish thali**, and mouth-watering **dal makhani** and **chicken kadai**—showcasing a delightful fusion of flavors that are sure to tantalize any palate.

### Ambiance & Design

As you approach the restaurant, you’re greeted by a vibrant and inviting exterior that sets a welcoming tone for diners. The interior boasts a beautifully designed space that offers both an air-conditioned room for comfort and an open-air section for those who prefer enjoying their meal al fresco. The layout strategically allows guests to soak in the pleasant coastal breeze, making it an ideal dining spot at any time of the day. Photos highlight tasteful decorations with hints of Punjabi culture, and soft lighting enhances the relaxed atmosphere, perfect for a delightful culinary experience.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The menu at Punjabi Kitchen is a treasure trove for food enthusiasts. Signature dishes such as the flavorful fish curry and diverse fish thali come highly recommended, alongside stalwarts like dal makhani and chicken kadai that are acclaimed for their rich, authentic flavors. Diners rave about the generous portions that leave them delightfully stuffed, with one reviewer humorously describing the aftermath of their indulgence as needing to be "rolled out like a giant exercise ball.” The food presentation reflects a careful attention to detail, as illustrated in the vibrant dishes captured in customer photos, showcasing colorful curries paired with perfect sides—definitely an Instagram-worthy experience. 

From the perspective of dietary options, Punjabi Kitchen offers a sensible selection catering to various preferences, though specific mentions of vegetarian or vegan adaptations weren't highlighted in the reviews.

### Customer Experience & Service

The restaurant prides itself on efficient and friendly service, with reviewers often noting the attentiveness of the staff. One customer appreciated the promptness of their meal, arriving shortly after they ordered in an environment that wasn’t too rushed. The team seemingly embodies a spirit of hospitality that makes diners feel welcomed—an essential component of any great dining experience. While some diners might visit just for a late-night meal, this restaurant accommodates different schedules, offering reasonable hours that make it a reliable choice for night owls.

### Popularity & Reviews

Punjabi Kitchen has become a talked-about venue in the Calangute area, as evidenced by the sheer number of reviews and high rating. Social media also buzzes with appreciation as customers share their experiences and delicious finds. Although no specific critic ratings or awards were noted, the overwhelmingly positive sentiment suggests that Punjabi Kitchen has carved a niche for itself among Goan culinary offerings.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The reviews are accompanied by captivating visuals that highlight both the restaurant’s inviting atmosphere and its delectable dishes. Pictures of the colorful curries and the elegantly arranged plates really bring the menu to life, making one want to dive right into the experience. For instance, images depict vibrant thalis and sizzling plates that embody the essence of North Indian cuisine—each snapshot promising an undeniable feast for both the eyes and the taste buds.

### Conclusion

If you find yourself wandering through Calangute, Punjabi Kitchen Bar & Restaurant is a must-visit destination. With its rich array of flavors, inviting ambiance, and a stellar service team, it promises a dining experience that celebrates the best of Indian cuisine in the heart of Goa. From hearty breakfasts to late-night meals, the eclectic mix of savory dishes will surely linger in your memory long after the last bite is savored.
